text: Crook County is a county in the northeastern part of the U.S. state of Wyoming. As of the 2020 census, 7,181 people lived there, which makes it the third-least populous county in Wyoming. Its county seat is Sundance. It was formed on December 8, 1875. == Communities == === Towns === * Hulett * Moorcroft * Pine Haven * Sundance (county seat) === Census-designated place === * Beulah === Unincorporated communities === * Aladdin * Alva * Colony * Devils Tower * Farrall * Moskee * New Haven * Oshoto * Sand Creek Crossing * Stroner == References == == Other websites == * * Category:19th-century establishments in Wyoming Category:1875 establishments in the United States Category:Wyoming counties
